Pushes it into the leg side, to the right of midwicket who runs across, picks up and fires at the non-striker's end in one smooth motion. The replays show he was ambling across lazily. commentary: Amir Hamza to Porterfield, no run appeal for stumping and they go upstairs to refer it. It was pushed across and drifting outside off. Nice, tossed up, loopy delivery, tempting him into the front foot drive. The batsman comes forward and the ball beats the outside edge. His backfoot comes out slightly and Shahzad is quick to take the bails off. He has slid it back in but the question is if part of the foot was inside the line. Seems like they need another angle. Seems like a part of the foot is inside the line from one angle, but the other angle suggests on the line. Who will the benefit of doubt go to? It goes to the batsman

commentary: Amir Hamza to Stirling, no run oh, what a delivery. That's a dream of a delivery. On a length and spinning away after drawing the batsman forward. The wicketkeeper takes the bails off and they go up in appeal for a stumping. Seems like the backfoot has come up and this seems touch and go. Has he just planted a toe in when the bails are off? Remember, he has already had a life. This is really close. And it seems like the toe has just been put back in, green light comes on and Afghanistan have to wait further to get a breakthrough

Seems like the backfoot has come up and this seems touch and go. Has he just planted a toe in when the bails are off? Remember, he has already had a life. This is really close.
